    With an understanding of the message structure and field semantics of MegaD’s protocol messages, it became apparent
    that the C&C of MegaD is split into three servers. There exists a C&C server which provides instructions to bots
    when probed; an SMTP server which is used to test the spamming capabilities of bots, the hostname of which is sent
    to bots by the C&C server; and finally a spam server which bots download their spam templates from, the details of
    which are also supplied by the C&C server.

